verbose_text: Of note, the Gardos channel, also known as the intermediate conductance Ca 2+ -activated K + channel, K Ca 3.1, KCNN4, or SK4, is expressed in other cell types, such as T- and B-lymphocytes, macrophages, endothelial cells, fibroblasts, vascular smooth muscle cells, and neurons.
